# Decision-Surfacing Protocol (Copilot CLI — prompt-level)

Follow this protocol whenever an implementer or reviewer task is dispatched.
The floor installer writes this prompt guidance into the repository and leaves
global hook registration to explicit operator review.

## Subagent payload contract (Phase 3a)

Scoping pass MUST return a JSON payload between ` ```decision-payload ` fences:

```json
{
  "status": "NEEDS_DECISIONS",
  "scope": { "task_id": "...", "task_title": "..." },
  "decisions": [
    { "id": "d1", "title": "...", "context": "...",
      "options": [{"label":"...","description":"..."}, ...],
      "recommended_index": 0, "reasoning": "..." }
  ]
}
```

If no architecture / spec-ambiguity decisions: return `{"status":"NO_DECISIONS","scope":{...}}` instead.

Constraints: 2-4 options per decision; `recommended_index` mandatory; no file edits during scoping pass.

Implementer reports must include `verification_passed` before `STATUS: DONE`.
Reviewer reports must include `VERIFICATION_AUDIT: passed|failed|skipped`.
